tags: MY HEART IS GOING TO EXPLODE INTO RAINBOWS
Justice for Nicholas J Fury please and thank you
summary:
You know how basically every Marvel superhero movie has at least one 
'everyman' character who's the audience's window into the...
body:
You know how basically every Marvel superhero movie has at least one ‘everyman’ character who’s the audience’s window into the world, to anchor us while the superhero does their thing?

I keep realizing that in Captain Marvel that’s going to be Nick Fury and getting overcome with emotion all over again.

All this time, people acted like Nick was practically a villain for focusing on what needs to be done to save the world instead of coddling individuals, and now we’re getting a movie that straight-up views him as our very human connection to the universe.

Two hours of movie won’t undo ten years of fandom bashing him, but damn, it’s going to be beautiful to see.

summary: When I was younger my first experience buying comics in “bulk” was through yard sales and swap meet visits. I’d mostly buy...
body:
When I was younger my first experience buying comics in “bulk” was through yard sales and swap meet visits. I’d mostly buy covers that I thought were cool. I was about 9 so the idea of being a collector wasn’t solidified yet. I’d rummaged through stacks and boxes. Many of the issues were torn or not in the best of condition so I got them for one time reads.

My first introduction to Carol Danvers was in Uncanny X-Men issue 187. At this stage in her character she was Binary. She opened the door for me to meet Rogue and learn about their uncomfortable history.
